            "id": "3c6de113993645b09fd6b",
            "questionText": "A research submarine uses sonar to map the ocean floor. The submarine is $!$750\\text{ m}$!$ above the ocean floor, and it emits an ultrasound pulse with a frequency of $!$40\\text{ kHz}$!$ that produces an echo received after $!$1\\text{ s}$!$. Calculate the wavelength (in meters) of the sound waves in water.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "c023a6a84a7d46aebdce5",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct sonar echo formula that relates the distance to the ocean floor, the speed of sound, and the total travel time of the pulse. Choose the formula that is used for such echo-based distance calculations.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "670671d3-985c-4a23-9178-05e06ebd3f7b"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ d = \\frac{v t}{2} $!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ d = v t $!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ d = \\frac{2v}{t} $!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "b9a3cc1fb08946a5b371f",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, using the selected formula and the information provided (a distance of $!$750\\text{ m}$!$ and a total echo time of $!$1\\text{ s}$!$), calculate the speed of sound in water by rearranging the formula appropriately.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "1500"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m/s",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "670671d3-985c-4a23-9178-05e06ebd3f7b"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "d4945c69fae8494485046",
                    "stepText": "Now that you have the speed, let\u2019s identify the correct relationship between the wave's speed, frequency, and wavelength. Select the formula that correctly relates these quantities.",
